{
  "stem": "2316.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the first thing I remember-- and this is really a true story.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was a young kid and I remember getting up in the morning and I told my father that-- I was very close with my dad.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I always told him stories.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I told him I dreamt there was a war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because people were talking anyway, and I think what you hear, so I dreamt about it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I says, there's a war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that same day on the radio they announced that the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the first-- the first thing that happened is we didn't have industry to bomb or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I remember the planes flying over the shtetl, and the bombs were dropping out of nowhere.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, they came out and everybody started running into the woods.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were-- the Radziwill woods were right in back of our shtetl all over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so everybody was running away to the woods, or hiding in the gardens, or just lying down, wherever they could.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I don't know how many bombs were dropping, but it was just-- I've never heard anything like this in my life.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Noises, and the sound of the bombs, and the screams, and the hysterics of the mothers, and babies, and children.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I was hiding next door in the garden, and then I saw a bomb drop and kill my goat, my brother's goat, actually.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that was-- that was absolutely the worst thing I ever witnessed in my entire life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I thought that was-- that was a Holocaust to me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it was my brother's goat and he was beside himself.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
